Text.SourceString: I wouldn’t be too worried about being bad at fishing. It’s one of those things that improve with practice.
Text.LocalizedString: I wouldn’t be too worried about being bad at fishing. It’s one of those things that improve with practice.

Text.SourceString: I fish after work when I don’t feel too tired. I suppose that’s the problem with being an old man. Even fun seems like hard work.
Text.LocalizedString: I fish after work when I don’t feel too tired. I suppose that’s the problem with being an old man. Even fun seems like hard work.

Text.SourceString: There are all kinds of different fish. Some of them are only out at night, so you need to keep the timing in mind if you’re looking for something specific.

Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know how you do it, walking around in the snow and the cold.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know how you do it, walking around in the snow and the cold.

Text.SourceString: You’ll eventually find out who everyone really is if you give it some time. Some you’ll get along with, and some you won’t, and that’s okay.
Text.LocalizedString: You’ll eventually find out who everyone really is if you give it some time. Some you’ll get along with, and some you won’t, and that’s okay.

Text.SourceString: What do you need here, farmer?
Text.LocalizedString: What do you need here, farmer?

Text.LocalizedString: My knees hurt. I think I may have been walking too fast.

Text.LocalizedString: If it isn’t your knees, it’s your hips. That’s old age for ya, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.LocalizedString: There are fish that you can only catch on rainy days.//You need to know these things.

Text.SourceString: There are night fish as well.//There should be information about fish and bugs on TV.
Text.LocalizedString: There are night fish as well.//There should be information about fish and bugs on TV.

Text.SourceString: I usually order hot tea at the Tavern. Beer is not for me.
Text.LocalizedString: I usually order hot tea at the Tavern. Beer is not for me.

Text.SourceString: And if I had my way, it wouldn’t be for my children either.//<portrait=normal>But we live in a different era now.
Text.LocalizedString: And if I had my way, it wouldn’t be for my children either.//<portrait=normal>But we live in a different era now.

Text.SourceString: Those empty shells are worth quite a bit, and new ones wash ashore just about every day.
Text.LocalizedString: Those empty shells are worth quite a bit, and new ones wash ashore just about every day.

Text.SourceString: Do you know what I’m talking about? Cockle, murex. That kind.//<portrait=normal>You’ll get a lot for them.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know what I’m talking about? Cockle, murex. That kind.//<portrait=normal>You’ll get a lot for them.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Lily’s</> never been any trouble. Now or when she was little.//<portrait=happy>She’s a good kid.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Lily’s</> never been any trouble. Now or when she was little.//<portrait=happy>She’s a good kid.

Text.SourceString: She doesn’t talk very much. She looks like her mother, but she got her personality from me. Should I be worried?
Text.LocalizedString: She doesn’t talk very much. She looks like her mother, but she got her personality from me. Should I be worried?

Text.SourceString: You can catch king salmon at sea on Summer nights. I picked up that little piece of info in my fishing days.
Text.LocalizedString: You can catch king salmon at sea on Summer nights. I picked up that little piece of info in my fishing days.

Text.SourceString: The lake and creeks around town are rich with fish.
Text.LocalizedString: The lake and creeks around town are rich with fish.

Text.SourceString: What are you doing here, kid?
Text.LocalizedString: What are you doing here, kid?

Text.SourceString: I don’t recommend eating shells like the ones scattered on the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t recommend eating shells like the ones scattered on the beach.

Text.SourceString: You can sell those, but maybe don’t eat them.//Eat fish instead.
Text.LocalizedString: You can sell those, but maybe don’t eat them.//Eat fish instead.

Text.SourceString: I don’t force my children to do anything. But surely, offering simple guidance to make sure they take the right path in life doesn’t count as forcing.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t force my children to do anything. But surely, offering simple guidance to make sure they take the right path in life doesn’t count as forcing.

Text.SourceString: I think not guiding them would be unfatherly.//That would make me a bad parent.
Text.LocalizedString: I think not guiding them would be unfatherly.//That would make me a bad parent.

Text.SourceString: I know my son is having a hard time letting his mother go, even after all these years.//<portrait=concerned>It makes me sad to see him hurting, but…
Text.LocalizedString: I know my son is having a hard time letting his mother go, even after all these years.//<portrait=concerned>It makes me sad to see him hurting, but…

Text.SourceString: I also know with <NpcName>Theo</>, you can’t force him.//He’d just shut his door tighter. Being patient is the best thing I can do for him.//And it’s so hard.
Text.LocalizedString: I also know with <NpcName>Theo</>, you can’t force him.//He’d just shut his door tighter. Being patient is the best thing I can do for him.//And it’s so hard.

Text.SourceString: I overheard <NpcName>Lily</> talking to her mother last night.//It broke my heart. My poor girl.
Text.LocalizedString: I overheard <NpcName>Lily</> talking to her mother last night.//It broke my heart. My poor girl.

Text.SourceString: I can’t make anybody see what they don’t see, especially <NpcName>Theo</>.//It hurts to see him suffering, but I can’t make him talk to me if he doesn’t want to.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t make anybody see what they don’t see, especially <NpcName>Theo</>.//It hurts to see him suffering, but I can’t make him talk to me if he doesn’t want to.

Text.SourceString: What do you do now? Surely you can’t farm in Winter?
Text.LocalizedString: What do you do now? Surely you can’t farm in Winter?

Text.SourceString: Ha! <NpcName>Sam</> said that, didn’t he? His head is bigger than I thought.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha! <NpcName>Sam</> said that, didn’t he? His head is bigger than I thought.

Text.SourceString: Let me tell you my side of things. Sure, <NpcName>Sam</> beats me at chess, but it’s only because I’m usually too busy to play more than one game.//I’m not in the right frame of mind to play.
Text.LocalizedString: Let me tell you my side of things. Sure, <NpcName>Sam</> beats me at chess, but it’s only because I’m usually too busy to play more than one game.//I’m not in the right frame of mind to play.

Text.SourceString: Ha ha! Sure. You can tell him I said that.
Text.LocalizedString: Ha ha! Sure. You can tell him I said that.

Text.SourceString: You do come here a lot, don’t you?//That’s nice.
Text.LocalizedString: You do come here a lot, don’t you?//That’s nice.

Text.SourceString: You’re not supposed to be back here.//Cook only.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re not supposed to be back here.//Cook only.

Text.SourceString: You certainly come to the house a lot, don’t you? Are you looking for my children?//I heard you’re friends.
Text.LocalizedString: You certainly come to the house a lot, don’t you? Are you looking for my children?//I heard you’re friends.

Text.SourceString: It’s inevitable for us to get visitors, I suppose. Having to live in town and all.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s inevitable for us to get visitors, I suppose. Having to live in town and all.

Text.SourceString: Did you just walk in here?//Well then, welcome.
Text.LocalizedString: Did you just walk in here?//Well then, welcome.

Text.SourceString: Excuse me. I’m late.
Text.LocalizedString: Excuse me. I’m late.

Text.SourceString: You smell that?//I’m making fish stew.
Text.LocalizedString: You smell that?//I’m making fish stew.
